  • Constructor Details

    • PlayerMove

      public PlayerMove​(java.lang.String workerId, TurnEvents.Actions move, Position targetPosition, java.lang.String currentPlayerNickname)
      Constructor of the message PlayerMove, required to send the information regarding the move performed by the player during the game.
      Parameters:
      workerId - The ID of the worker chosen by the player to play with this turn.
      move - The Actions performed by the player.
      targetPosition - The position of the target slot chose by the player for the current move.
      currentPlayerNickname - The nickname of the current player.
